<li><h3>2.	Timberrrr</h3>
	<br>
<p class="bloglist">With Trump’s new tariff on Canadian softwood lumber, American builders will start to see increasing costs for production and job losses in the thousands seems likely on the Canadian side. That’s not to mention the potential effect on Canada’s GDP as softwood lumber exports to the U.S., though, not as prominent as it once was, still plays a large role.
Check out what the new tariff means for your province here:
<br>
<a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2017/04/27/trump-lumber-tariff-canada_n_16298756.html" alt="Trump Lumber Tariff Canada">Read More</a></p>
<br>
