<br><br>
</li>
<li><h3>3.	The REIT Stuff</h3>
	<br>
<p class="bloglist">This week there have been a number of REIT announcements from awards to acquisitions. See some of the latest ones below:</p>
<br><br>
<p class="bloglist">-Artis Real Estate Investment Trust was announced as one of Canada's Top Small and Medium Employers for 2017. The award recognizes the small and medium enterprises that offer the nation's best workplaces and forward-thinking human resources policies. Some of the criteria include: physical workspace, work & social atmosphere, benefits, and training and skills development. Congratulations Artis!
<br>
<a href="http://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/artis-real-estate-investment-trust-named-one-of-canadas-top-small-and-medium-employers-for-2017-620387453.html">Read Artis's press release here</a></p>
<br><br>
<p class="bloglist">̶̶Agellan Commercial Real Estate Investment Trust acquired an industrial distribution facility in Flint, Michigan. It’s fully leased to General Motors and as anyone who hasn’t been under a rock the past few months would wonder, the press release claims “the water supply for the Distribution Facility is provided by the local township, the Distribution Facility has not been directly affected by recent water issues identified in the City of Flint.”
<br>
<a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/agellan-commercial-real-estate-investment-135800126.html">Read about the acqusition here</a></p>
<br><br>
<p class="bloglist">-In more dire news, Canadian Apartment Properties Real Estate Investment Trust President and Chief Executive Officer, Thomas Schwartz has been diagnosed with prostate cancer. Taking time to focus on his health and recover, Mr. Schwartz’s doctors are optimistic about his recovery and in the meantime Michael Stein, Chair of CAPREIT, will help coordinate CAPREIT's management team until Mr. Schwartz can fully return to work.
<br>
<a href="http://www.montrealgazette.com/business/cnw/release.html?rkey=20170425C2939&filter=5611">More details on CAPREIT here</a></p>
</li>
<br>
<li><h3>4.	If We Build It, Will They Come?</h3>
	<br>
<p class="bloglist">The Ontario Liberal government has rolled out a new proposed budget ahead of the June 2018 election; in it is a plan to grow infrastructure in Ontario’s health care and educational system. An additional $30 billion is allocated towards new hospital projects, school renewal, and child care expansion.
	<br>
<a href="http://dailycommercialnews.com/en-US/Infrastructure/News/2017/4/Province-commits-billions-to-hospital-school-construction-in-budget-1023480W/">Click here for more details on the proposed budget</a></p>
