<h2>Upcoming Events</h2>
<br>
<h3>May 10 - May 11: <a href="http://www.realtor-quest.ca/index.php">TREB REALTOR QUEST</a></h3>
<br>
<p style="margin-top:-3%" class="blogloca">Toronto Congress Centre, Toronto, Ontario</p>
<p class="p-events">Join over 8,000 real estate professionals for REALTOR® QUEST, Canada's largest REALTOR® Trade Show and Conference. Central to the trade show is the REALTOR® QUEST Centre Stage which will feature an impressive array of live entertainment, video presentations, and unique opportunities for sponsor networking and involvement. Complementing the REALTOR® QUEST trade show will be Health Quest, Learning Quest sessions, TREB's Spring Annual Meeting of Members and more.
</p>
<br>
<h3>May 16 – May 18: <a href="http://marketplacetoronto.com">International Real Estate Marketplace</a></h3>
<p class="blogloca">Metro Toronto Convention Centre, Toronto, Ontario</p>
<p class="p-events">Canadian International Real Estate Marketplace, Canada's first-ever international property investment trade show will take place on May 16th to the 18th, 2017 at the Metro Toronto Convention Centre.
The show will be open to the Canadian public and over 40,000 VIP investors (Royal, political, and high net worth individuals) who will be invited to this prestigious event.
</p>
<br>
<h3>May 17: <a href="http://www.rahb.ca/event/master-open-house-4/?instance_id=1028">MASTER Open House</a></h3>
<p class="blogloca">RAHB, Hamilton, Ontario</p>
<p class="p-events">This interactive course is designed to take you from holding an average open house to becoming a MASTER at open houses. Topics include: marketing your Open House online using social media, develop a take-home kit, get more prospects to show up, and more</p>
<br>
<h3>May 19: <a href="http://www.rahb.ca/event/insurance-concerns-for-buyers/?instance_id=1035">Insurance Concerns for Buyers</a></h3>
<p class="blogloca">RAHB, Hamilton, Ontario</p>
<p class="p-events">This presentation will address some of the challenges facing buyers when they try to obtain insurance for the purchase of their home. There is a discussion of the different issues that arise when deficiencies are discovered, such as knob and tube wiring or underground oil tanks.  Further there is discussion about the protections that are available to the real estate in form of clauses to be inserted into Agreements of Purchase and Sale.</p>
<br>
<h3>May 21 – May 24: <a href="http://www.icsc.org/recon/">ICSC RECon </a></h3>
<p class="blogloca">Las Vegas, Nevada</p>
<p class="p-events">RECon is the world’s largest retail real estate convention with more than 37,000 attendees representing 58 countries who gather for power deal making, endless networking and innovative education.
This makes RECon the premier gathering place for retail real estate professionals to conduct a year’s worth of business in just three days!  No other convention will give your company this unprecedented depth of exposure and reach.
</p>
<br>
<h3>Jun 7 – Jun 9: <a href="http://accelerate.vts.com/">Accelerate</a></h3>
<p class="blogloca">New York, New York</p>
<p class="p-events">The Commercial Real Estate Innovation Conference<br>
Join VTS and the industry’s most influential thought leaders to learn how technology is shaping the future of commercial real estate. Collaborate with the experts on the forefront of innovation and hear first hand how technology is changing the way we do business.</p>
